# .dockerignore — keep the (standalone) build context to what the image needs.
#
# Dockerfile.base only COPYs: configs/, scripts/, overrides/.
# Everything below is documentation, tooling, or per-project scaffolding that
# must NOT bloat the build context or leak into the image.

# Other docs (human-facing, never baked into the image):
README.md
CLAUDE.md
SCRIPTS.md
CHANGELOG.md

# Templates / scaffolding consumed at the project level, not by the build:
compose.base.yml
compose.example.yml
.env.example
.env.wordpress.example
VERSION

# VCS, CI, and local dev tooling:
.git
.gitignore
.github
.githooks

# Editor / OS / local artifacts:
.idea
.vscode
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*.log
.cache